def: An affection of the kidneys, usually inflammatory in character,and distinguished by the occurrence of albumin and renal casts in theurine. Several varieties of Bright's disease are now recognized,differing in the part of the kidney involved, and in the intensityand course of the morbid process.

An unsaturated hydrocarbon, C8H8, obtained by the distillationof storax, by the decomposition of cinnamic acid, and by thecondensation of acetylene, as a fragrant, aromatic, mobile liquid; --called also phenyl ethylene, vinyl benzene, styrol, styrene, andcinnamene.
One of the dominant people of Hungary, allied to the Finns; aHungarian.
One who, or that which, deprives.
A form of speech adapted to be used by all mankind; universallanguage.
Capable of being repugned or resisted. [R.] Sir T. North.
Like lava, or composed of lava; lavic.
The process of generation by development of blastema, orfission of cells, in which the new formation is in all respect likethe individual from which it proceeds.
Crabbed; difficult, or perplexing. "Persius is crabby, becauseancient." Marston.
A female maker of, or dealer in, articles of fashion,especially of the fashionable dress of ladies; a woman who givesdirection to the style or mode of dress.
